The paper proposes a new deep neural architecture for object recognition, which is a common task in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The proposed architecture involves multiple parallel subnetworks and a competition mechanism, which are related to deep learning (LG), artificial intelligence (AI), and neural networks (NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the encoding of category information, which is relevant to natural language processing (CL).
